name: SubstanceOtherThanClinicalDrug
title: Substance Other Than Clinical Drug
description:
Removed these previously used exclusions because some concepts must come from SCT due to removal of UNII as part of the grouped value sets used in 2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1010.1  Substance Reactant for intoleranceDescendantsAndSelf (438951008|Substance categorized by hazard characteristics|), DescendantsAndSelf (312412007|Substance categorized functionally|), DescendantsAndSelf (312413002|Substance categorized structurally|), DescendantsAndSelf (312417001|Substance of abuse|)
2018-11-03 changed per http://www.hl7.org/dstucomments/showdetail_comment.cfm?commentid=1596
purpose:
(Clinical Focus: Created for allergy intolerance substance representation, this value set has substances that are not represented by RXNORM  drug concepts or FDA UNII substance concepts. This value set is meant to be quite broad and includes many substances that may never be prescribed or be a reactant. It is intended to be a final "catch-all" value set for concepts not found in RXNORM and does not remove codes that overlap with RxNorm so this value set should be used last when searching.),(Data Element Scope: Substance elements),(Inclusion Criteria: Descendants of (105590001|Substance| OR 41355003|Ultraviolet radiation | OR 84489001 |Mold) and other specific codes as needed
The product code 424369009 | Product containing beta-galactosidase (medicinal product) was specifically included in a prior version.),(Exclusion Criteria: Concepts that are best represented using RxNorm)
